                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>To the <addressee>Rd I. Leeser</addressee></p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Dr Sir</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\">I am desired by <persName>Mr. Mayard<add>?</add> Myers</persName> to\n                forward the enclosed for publication<lb/> in the first Occident. I may mention that\n                these gentlmn “furnished” me with the materials<lb/> for this composition our time\n                    <sic>as</sic> been fully occupied the last week in various\n                <sic>unfortun</sic><lb/> ways we had only <date>Saturday</date> Evg to examine its\n                contents, and which proves to be very defective<lb/> in many respects my time was\n                employed as <add>Hebrew</add> the last week we had a great<lb/> mortality among the\n                children “I am assured by <persName>Mr. Mayer</persName> that you will be good\n                enough<lb/> to correct the many errors Which I have made &amp; unable to repair at\n                last be <sic>pleas</sic><lb/> to round off sharp corners of the improper\n                sentences.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I regret that we are unable to do justice in answering the Bnai\n                Jeshurun or<lb/> in the manner they desired<add>?</add> bad it is it <sic>is</sic> a\n                touch of yr. pen may be the means of opening<lb/> the closed eyes of that community.\n                Your beautiful leading Act. in the last <date>Oct.</date><lb/> has <sic>coold</sic>\n                the Ardor they <sic>to</sic> eagerly derived for a paper war<del>fare</del>. I hope\n                this &amp; the<lb/> communication which I am told will be sent you from one of our\n                members will<lb/> decide the battle.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(7)\">I am Dr. Sir</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(8)\">Yours very resfy</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(9)\">\n                <persName role=\"author\">Saml. Bruel</persName>\n            </p>\n            <p>\n                <date>18 Ap.</date>\n            </p>\n            <p>in hopes of being in time for this mo-</p>\n            <p>This <sic>letters</sic> have references to the article.</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3hm5322v/canvas/p1"
                }
